The Gauteng roads and transport department is under fire for allegedly issuing a tender to build a road on top of Transnet petrol pipelines. The site of the proposed road is behind the Total Petro Port service station on the N3 road, between Heidelberg and Alberton in Ekurhuleni. Lawyers acting on behalf of environmental activists have sent a letter to the department demanding construction be halted pending a review application challenging the validity of the environmental authorisation for the road. In the letter, addressed to the departmentâ€™s chief director, Freeman Masuku, the activists demand the department undertakes not to start...